title: For Sale/Trade:  Beretta 92 "Step Slide" 1st Edition -Rare-
postcontent: I have for sale/trade a very rare First Edition Beretta 92 "Step Slide" 9mm semi-automatic Italian pistol. The first Beretta 92 series pistols were made in Italy in the late 70's and of those only the first couple thousand included what they call a step slide. The step slide was a weight reducing feature used to better balance the pistol. As you can see the Original Beretta 92's also have a 1911 style frame safety which many shooters prefer(Notice the coveted limted edition Beretta Centennials also include this feature). In addition, they have a euro style bottom mag release, rounded trigger guard, and rich Italian bluing. I have only ever seen one other of these for sale stateside and it fetched several thousand dollars. This is your chance to own a true piece of history and now that Sig Sauer won the new Military Contract the Beretta 92's 30+ year U.S Military reign is soon coming to an end and these rare pistols will only increase in collector value. This pistol is in excellent unmolested condition and comes with one original magazine and carrying case. Price is $2500/Trade. Thanks
